<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,477,1332]" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">
Macropterous or micropterous 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Uzel" authorityYear="1895" box="[495,675,477,503]" class="Insecta" family="Phlaeothripidae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Thysanoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="422" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subFamily" subFamily="Phlaeothripinae">Phlaeothripinae</taxonomicName>
; head slightly longer than wide (
<figureCitation box="[1034,1101,477,503]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1637,1662]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,179,1609]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1609]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Drypetothrips korykis gen et sp. n. and galls. (1) Drypetes deplanchei leaf margin galls; (2) holotype head and pronotum; (3) meso and metanotum; (4) antenna; (5) prosternites; (6) tergite IX and tube; (7) pelta and tergites II–IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741290" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741290/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Fig. 2</figureCitation>
), with 2 pairs of long, capitate po setae, compound eyes equally large dorsally and ventrally; maxillary stylets wide apart and V-shaped, retracted about half-way to po setae. Antennae 8-segmented (
<figureCitation box="[741,811,549,575]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1637,1662]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,179,1609]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1609]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Drypetothrips korykis gen et sp. n. and galls. (1) Drypetes deplanchei leaf margin galls; (2) holotype head and pronotum; (3) meso and metanotum; (4) antenna; (5) prosternites; (6) tergite IX and tube; (7) pelta and tergites II–IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741290" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741290/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
), III with 1 sense cone, IV with 3 sense cones; IV–VII each with narrow, parallel-sided pedicel. Pronotum with 5 pairs of major setae, am setae longer than aa setae, notopleural sutures complete; metanotum reticulate. Prosternal basantra absent, ferna irregularly sub-circular (
<figureCitation box="[1351,1421,621,648]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1637,1662]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,179,1609]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1609]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Drypetothrips korykis gen et sp. n. and galls. (1) Drypetes deplanchei leaf margin galls; (2) holotype head and pronotum; (3) meso and metanotum; (4) antenna; (5) prosternites; (6) tergite IX and tube; (7) pelta and tergites II–IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741290" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741290/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
); mesopresternum weakly complete medially or reduced to pair of lateral triangles; metathoracic sternopleural sutures present. Fore femora stout, fore tarsal tooth as long as tarsal width. Fore wing parallel sided, with 3 capitate subbasal setae, without duplicated cilia. Pelta broadly triangular, wider than long (
<figureCitation box="[1022,1090,729,756]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1637,1662]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,179,1609]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1609]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Drypetothrips korykis gen et sp. n. and galls. (1) Drypetes deplanchei leaf margin galls; (2) holotype head and pronotum; (3) meso and metanotum; (4) antenna; (5) prosternites; (6) tergite IX and tube; (7) pelta and tergites II–IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741290" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741290/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Fig. 7</figureCitation>
), campaniform sensilla usually absent, sometimes replaced by a minute seta; tergites II–VII each with 2 pairs of weakly sigmoid wing-retaining setae placed laterally, posterior pair on each tergite unusually long; tergite VIII with posteromarginal and posteroangular setal pairs as long as median length of tergite; tergite IX setae S1 and S2 slightly shorter than tube, tube slightly longer than head (
<figureCitation box="[447,516,873,900]" captionStart="FIGURES 1–7" captionStartId="2.[151,264,1637,1662]" captionTargetBox="[152,1435,179,1609]" captionTargetId="figure@2.[151,1435,179,1609]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURES 1–7. Drypetothrips korykis gen et sp. n. and galls. (1) Drypetes deplanchei leaf margin galls; (2) holotype head and pronotum; (3) meso and metanotum; (4) antenna; (5) prosternites; (6) tergite IX and tube; (7) pelta and tergites II–IV." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3741290" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3741290/files/figure.png" pageId="1" pageNumber="422">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). Male micropterous, similar to female microptera and with ocelli present; tergite IX setae S2 variable in length 0.5–1.0 as long as setae S1; sternite VIII with no pore plate.
</paragraph>
